It appears that it is already _supposed_ to do that, but clearly isn't. See [Compare-Object.cs L374](https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/3ab605aeec1dbd5a9e975f15628b0648b6ee0464/src/Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.Utility/commands/utility/Compare-Object.cs#L374):

```csharp
/// <summary>
/// If the parameter 'ExcludeDifferent' is present, then we need to turn on the
/// 'IncludeEqual' switch unless it's turned off by the user specifically.
/// </summary>
protected override void BeginProcessing()
{
    if (ExcludeDifferent)
    {
        if (_isIncludeEqualSpecified == false)
        {
            return;
        }

        if (_isIncludeEqualSpecified && !_includeEqual)
        {
            return;
        }

        _includeEqual = true;
    }
}
```
